> grab a shiny brass idol ( I feel like a broken record ) for the trip too.  That 14 seconds invunerable can be used to dash to the book if there is a see invis mob standing infront of it and give you heaps of time to grab the book and invis.<br>
<br>
Tizla <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaeildylanena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caeildy Lanena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 11:21:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> Duelling wont work. Res time is only 5 mins.<br>
<br>
Have a real death and accept the 96% res back if you're keen enough.<br>
<br>
Also, hide does not drop when you pick up the book. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unortherner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Northerner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/3/02 5:36:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> Even of you get out clean, an instant-gate potion is perhaps the most valuable thing you can ever own.  I still always carry a CT potion, it is an instant get-out-of-jail-free card.  I know where it is and in what bag and I'd bet I could whip it out and cast before Nimble ever wore off.<br>
<br>
Nah, I've eaten a few dozen deaths without burning it but having that available opens a world of possibilities.  Group with idiots (the ones you can't even trust for CR/Rezzes), go to planes p/u thingies... generally feel immortal.  In a pinch, actually hotkey the potion by putting it in a main slot and such.  Hihi, nearly unkillable here, /bird Lord Empirrrarrrrr Seru.<br>
<br>
That all said, take one on your jaunt and it's not really a nailbiter, it's a fun romp.  I always loved scouting PoH anyways and going from IZ to the book is a perfect compromise of tough and fun.  I'd wager anyone I can do it 9/10 though now that I know the way well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=syntero>syntero</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/02 11:24:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> Just wondering if anyone has a reliabe map... for someone who's never been to the zone....<br>
<br>
I haven't been able to locate one.<br>
<br>
Thanks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utillaintheslacker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tillain the Slacker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/02 12:02:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> BTW library had an excellent map of hate before, never checked lately but it was there. <br>
<br>
As far as the hate solo trip, it does break hide but doesn't break sneak. Have wizzie port up and gate out or evac if they are a chicken. You sneak up get book when mob is turned, re-hide sneak back to SS and cast your gate potion, Done. I know i have done it, btw for the ease of cost make Thurg gate potions they are easy to make and it may be a timed spell but you will gate out real easy sitting on wall. I have done it twice on a fully spawned hate, easy as pie. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=syntero>syntero</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/02 2:43:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4604.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic Quest Question! Maestros room.</span><hr size=1> *nods*<br>
